<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="147" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1451,1293,1534]" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">
<taxonomicName authority="Runemark ex Phitos" authorityName="Phitos" box="[136,660,1368,1390]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Campanula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="lyrata" subSpecies="icarica">
<emphasis box="[136,312,1368,1389]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Campanula lyrata</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[388,456,1368,1389]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">icarica</emphasis>
Runemark ex Phitos
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Damboldt, J." box="[701,892,1368,1390]" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" pagination="39 - 52" refId="ref1537" refString="Damboldt, J. (1976) Materials for a flora of Turkey xxxii: Campanulaceae. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh 35: 39 - 52." type="journal article" year="1976">Damboldt 1976: 44</bibRefCitation>
) is one of the species of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boiss.) Phitos" authorityName="Phitos" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Campanula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Quinqueloculares" subGenus="Campanula">
<emphasis box="[1139,1251,1368,1389]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Campanula</emphasis>
subgen. 
<emphasis box="[1339,1451,1368,1389]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Campanula</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis box="[238,409,1404,1425]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Quinqueloculares</emphasis>
(Boiss.) Phitos
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Damboldt, J." box="[591,780,1404,1426]" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" pagination="39 - 52" refId="ref1537" refString="Damboldt, J. (1976) Materials for a flora of Turkey xxxii: Campanulaceae. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh 35: 39 - 52." type="journal article" year="1976">Damboldt 1976: 40</bibRefCitation>
). This taxon was first described by D. Phitos from the Aegean island of Icaria (
<bibRefCitation author="Damboldt, J." box="[255,410,1440,1462]" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" pagination="39 - 52" refId="ref1537" refString="Damboldt, J. (1976) Materials for a flora of Turkey xxxii: Campanulaceae. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh 35: 39 - 52." type="journal article" year="1976">Damboldt 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Several specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[632,855,1440,1462]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Campanula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="lyrata" subSpecies="icarica">
<emphasis box="[632,716,1440,1461]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">C. lyrata</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[787,855,1440,1461]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">icarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected during fieldwork in 
<collectingRegion box="[1194,1246,1440,1462]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Izmir</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1290,1353,1440,1462]" country="Turkey" name="Mugla" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Muğla</collectingRegion>
provinces in 2019 which has not been previously recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[697,767,1476,1498]" name="Turkey" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. Despite Icaria’s proximity to 
<collectingCountry box="[1066,1136,1476,1498]" name="Turkey" pageId="0" pageNumber="147">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, there had been doubt about the presence of this taxon on the mainland (
<bibRefCitation author="Damboldt, J." box="[572,728,1512,1534]" pageId="0" pageNumber="147" refId="ref1568" refString="Damboldt, J. (1978) Campanula L. In: Davis, P. H. (Ed.) Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands, Vol. 6. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh, UK, pp. 2 - 64." type="book" year="1978">Damboldt 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
